10/07/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Parliament is expected to vote Friday (July 10th) on the reshuffle of Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski's cabinet. Education Minister Pero Stojanovski and Agriculture Minister Aco Spasenovski submitted their resignations, while Finance Minister Trajko Slavevski was replaced by Gruevski. If approved by parliament, Deputy Prime Minister Zoran Stavrevski will add the finance ministry to his portfolio; Nikola Todorov will be appointed education minister and Ljupco Dimovski will become agriculture minister. Deputy Prime Minister for European Integration Ivica Bocevski, who left the cabinet a week ago, will be replaced by Vasko Naumovski. (A1, Makfax, MIA - 09/07/09)
